====================================================================
üìå SQL NUMERIC & DATE FUNCTIONS (NOTES + EXAMPLES)
====================================================================

SQL provides **built-in functions** to perform operations on:
‚úî Numbers  
‚úî Dates & Time  

These functions help in:
‚úî Calculations  
‚úî Rounding values  
‚úî Date manipulation  
‚úî Formatting date & time  

====================================================================
BASIC DATABASE COMMANDS
--------------------------------------------------------------------
use world;
show tables;
====================================================================


====================================================================
# 1Ô∏è‚É£ NUMERIC FUNCTIONS
====================================================================

------------------------------------------------------------
üîπ ROUND()
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Used to round a number to nearest integer or decimal places.

SYNTAX:
ROUND(number, decimals)

EXAMPLES:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
select lifeexpectancy, round(lifeexpectancy) from country;

select 83.62, round(83.687, 2);      -- rounds to 2 decimal places

select 456.23, round(456.23, -2);    -- rounds to nearest hundred


------------------------------------------------------------
üîπ POWER FUNCTION ‚Üí POW()
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Used to calculate power of a number.

SYNTAX:
POW(base, exponent)

EXAMPLE:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
select pow(2,3);   -- Output: 8


------------------------------------------------------------
üîπ CEIL()
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Rounds a number **UP** to the nearest integer.

EXAMPLE:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
select ceil(3.0000008);   -- Output: 4


------------------------------------------------------------
üîπ FLOOR()
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Rounds a number **DOWN** to the nearest integer.

EXAMPLE:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
select floor(3.456);      -- Output: 3


====================================================================
# 2Ô∏è‚É£ DATE & TIME FUNCTIONS
====================================================================

------------------------------------------------------------
üîπ NOW(), CURDATE(), CURRENT_TIME()
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Used to get current date & time.

NOW() and CURRENT_TIMESTAMP() are SAME.

EXAMPLES:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
select now();                -- date + time
select curdate();            -- only date
select current_time();       -- only time
select current_timestamp();  -- date + time


------------------------------------------------------------
üîπ ADDDATE()
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Used to add days or months to a date.

SYNTAX:
ADDDATE(date, value)
ADDDATE(date, INTERVAL value unit)

EXAMPLES:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
select now(), adddate(now(), 2);              -- add 2 days

select now(), adddate(now(), interval 3 month); -- add 3 months


------------------------------------------------------------
üîπ EXTRACT()
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Used to extract specific part from date (year, month, week, etc.)

SYNTAX:
EXTRACT(unit FROM date)

EXAMPLE:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
select now(), extract(week from now());


------------------------------------------------------------
üîπ DATE_FORMAT()
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Used to format date into readable string format.

SYNTAX:
DATE_FORMAT(date, format)

EXAMPLE:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
select now(), date_format(now(), 
'month is %M & year is %Y');


====================================================================
COMMON DATE FORMAT SYMBOLS
--------------------------------------------------------------------
%Y ‚Üí Year (2025)  
%M ‚Üí Month name (January)  
%m ‚Üí Month number  
%d ‚Üí Day  
%H ‚Üí Hour  
%i ‚Üí Minutes  
%s ‚Üí Seconds  

====================================================================
SUMMARY
====================================================================
‚úî ROUND() ‚Üí rounds values  
‚úî POW() ‚Üí power calculation  
‚úî CEIL() ‚Üí upper rounding  
‚úî FLOOR() ‚Üí lower rounding  

‚úî NOW() ‚Üí current date & time  
‚úî CURDATE() ‚Üí current date  
‚úî ADDDATE() ‚Üí add days/months  
‚úî EXTRACT() ‚Üí get part of date  
‚úî DATE_FORMAT() ‚Üí custom date format  

‚úî Used heavily in:
   ‚Ä¢ Reports  
   ‚Ä¢ Analytics  
   ‚Ä¢ Data Cleaning  
   ‚Ä¢ DBMS & SQL Interviews  

END OF NOTES
